article.headline: Nevada 74, Fresno St. 70
article.story: RENO, Nev. -- Luke Babbitt scored 27 points and Armon Johnson had 19 to lead Nevada past Fresno State 74-70 on Wednesday night. Babbitt hit two free throws with 8.7 seconds left to seal the victory for the Wolf Pack (16-9, 8-4 Western Athletic Conference). Paul George scored 26 points and Sylvester Seay 22 for the Bulldogs (13-14, 6-7). A layup by Fresno State's Mike Ladd tied the game 66-66 with 5:40 to play. Babbitt then hit two free throws with 4:45 to go and two more with 4:01 to play to give Nevada a 70-66 lead. Both fouls were on Seay, fouling out the 6-foot-10 senior. Seay scored 18 points and George had 12 as Fresno State took a 43-37 halftime lead.
